	Pitt baits Clooney    
	 Los Angeles, Sept. 13 (PTI): When George Clooney was propositioned by an Italian journalist, he had no clue that the prank was set up by none other than his best friends, Brad Pitt and Matt Damon.       
	The actor was at a news conference in Venice when he was proposed by the Italian journalist who took off his pants to reveal his underwear which said Choose Me.      
	Later, Damon divulged on a TV show that he and Pitt had spread the rumour that Clooney was gay to play a prank on the actor.    
	Lohans guru: Britney    
	 Los Angeles (PTI): Actress Lindsay Lohan has revealed that the example set by pop star Britney Spears has taught her how to manage fame. The Mean Girls star said she always knew the pitfalls of fame, because she watched Spearss meteoric rise as a youngster, TV show Access Hollywood has reported. Everyone goes through tough times. I think Ive always kind of aspired to be like Britney Spears. Its kind of something you sign up for in the beginning and if you really want it, you know that comes with it, she said.                                                                                                                                                                       
